'''Michal Sadílek''' ({{IPA|cs|ˈmɪxal ˈsaɟiːlɛk}}; born 31 May 1999) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Czech First League]] club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].<ref name = "WF">{{WorldFootball.net|michal-sadilek}}</ref>

==Club career==
Sadílek made his professional debut in the [[Eerste Divisie]] for [[Jong PSV]] on 4 November 2016 in a game against [[Helmond Sport]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Weltfussball|url=http://www.weltfussball.com/spielbericht/eerste-divisie-2016-2017-helmond-sport-jong-psv/|title=Game Report by Weltfussball|date=4 November 2016}}</ref> On 7 August 2021, he joined [[FC Twente]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Twente]]|url=https://www.fctwente.nl/nieuws/fc-twente-huurt-michal-sadilek/|title=FC Twente huurt Michal Sadilek|date=7 August 2021|accessdate=30 September 2021|language=nl}}</ref> On 19 April 2022, the deal was made permanent as he signed a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|first=Leon|last=ten Voorde|title=FC Twente slaat grote slag: Michal Sadilek tekent voor twee jaar |url=https://www.tubantia.nl/fc-twente/fc-twente-slaat-grote-slag-michal-sadilek-tekent-voor-twee-jaar~a1efbe95/|website=Tubantia|date=19 April 2022|access-date=3 July 2022|language=nl}}</ref> On 2 June 2025, Sadílek signed a contract with [[Czech First League]] club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] until June 2028.<ref>{{cite news|first=Martin|last=Slabý|title=Do Slavie přichází Sadílek. Kromě Ligy mistrů ho čeká i derby proti bratrovi|url=https://www.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/fotbal-slavia-praha-michal-sadilek-prestup-reprezentace-derby.html|website=[[Deník]]|date=2 June 2025|access-date=9 June 2025|language=cs|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Having represented Czech Republic at all youth levels, Sadílek was called up to the Czech senior squad by coach [[Jaroslav Šilhavý]] in May 2019.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Tomáš|last=Kubánek|title=Hrát v základu? Toho bych se nezalekl, říká mladý "vysavač" z Eindhovenu Sadílek|url=https://www.lidovky.cz/sport/fotbal/hrat-v-zakladu-toho-bych-se-nezalekl-rika-mlady-vysavac-z-eindhovenu-sadilek.A190604_194224_ln-sport-fotbal_lar|website=[[Lidové noviny]]|date=5 June 2019|access-date=31 March 2020|language=cs}}</ref>

In May 2021, he was announced as one of the four additional players for the rescheduled [[UEFA Euro 2020]], if [[Ondřej Kúdela]] failed to appeal against a ten-match ban from [[UEFA]] due to an alleged racial slur.<ref>{{Cite news|title=V nominaci reprezentace na ME chybí Dočkal, Šilhavý čeká na Kúdelu|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/v-nominaci-reprezentace-na-me-chybi-dockal-silhavy-ceka-na-kudelu-502583/|url-status=dead|date=25 May 2021|access-date=19 July 2021|website=Eurofotbal|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210606080107/https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/v-nominaci-reprezentace-na-me-chybi-dockal-silhavy-ceka-na-kudelu-502583/|archive-date=6 June 2021}}</ref> Eventually, Sadílek got priority over [[Lukáš Kalvach]], [[Patrizio Stronati]] and [[David Pavelka]] and filled the last vacant place in the nomination.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Liberecký Sadílek zaplnil poslední volné místo v české nominaci na Euro|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/liberecky-sadilek-zaplnil-posledni-volne-misto-v-ceske-nominaci-na-euro-502791/|url-status=dead|date=27 May 2021|access-date=19 July 2021|website=Eurofotbal|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720212046/https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/liberecky-sadilek-zaplnil-posledni-volne-misto-v-ceske-nominaci-na-euro-502791/|archive-date=20 July 2021}}</ref>

Sadílek debuted with the senior [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]] on 4 June 2021, in a friendly 4–0 loss to [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Sadílek, nečekaně na Euru: Šance si vážím, po turnaji se chci posunout|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/euro-2021/michal-sadilek-debut-reprezentace-cesko-italie.A210605_170941_euro-2020_jic|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|date=6 June 2021|language=cs}}</ref>

Sadílek was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]] on 28 May 2024,<ref>{{cite news |date=28 May 2024 |title=Nominace reprezentace na přípravný kemp před EURO 2024 |trans-title=National team nominations for the preparatory camp before EURO 2024 |url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/nominace/nominace/836 |language=cs |publisher=[[Czech Football Association]] |access-date=28 May 2024}}</ref> but had to withdraw before the tournament after injuring his leg when falling off his tricycle.<ref name="NOS.nl">[https://nos.nl/artikel/2523956-sadilek-mist-ek-door-afdaling-met-driewielerkart-niet-door-fietsongeluk Sadílek mist EK door afdaling met driewielerkart, niet door fietsongeluk] NOS.nl, 10 juni 2024</ref><ref name="ISport">[https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/blesk-sport/448561/skandal-v-narodaku-sadilkovu-nehodu-na-trikolce-maskovali-cyklistikou-kdo-a-proc-lhal.html Skandál v nároďáku! Sadílkovu nehodu na tříkolce maskovali cyklistikou: Kdo a proč lhal?] isport.blesk.cz, 11 juni 2024</ref>

==Personal life==
His brother [[Lukáš Sadílek|Lukáš]] is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Čeká je ligový souboj. Ale jednou si chceme zahrát spolu, říkají bratři Sadílkové|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/lukas-sadilek-michal-sadilek-liberec-slovacko.A201207_584442_fotbal_rou|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|date=7 December 2020|language=cs}}</ref>

